<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-11-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-01-08T14:47:00-05:00" n="186" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                            <head>186. Editorial Note</head>
                            <p>At 7 p.m. Foreign Secretary <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Macmillan</persName> met with Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Dulles</persName> at the latter’s villa to
                                review the events of the day and discuss the Middle East. The only
                                record of this meeting is a one-sentence notation, which indicates
                                that <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MAD1">MacArthur</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BRR1">Bowie</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_PH1">Phleger</persName> were also present, in
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName>, <hi rend="italic">Recollections</hi>, page 32.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>